## Overview

HEY HEY and happy holidays yall. When I heard DataStax was doing a 12 days of Codemas challenge, well you KNOW your boy had to take a crack at it; however, this time with some help with a couple of friends. What better way to do that than a [Christmas Cookie Recipe Finder](https://proto-pulsar-3qmym5m9z-jasonetorres-projects.vercel.app/)! It‚Äôs a web application that allows users to search for cookie recipes. I used Astro and React for the frontend, and DataStax‚Äôs own Astra DB as the backend to store and retrieve recipe data. The application is designed to be responsive and user-friendly.

**BUT‚Ä¶..**

since This is a Christmas build and I didn‚Äôt have much to go on, THIS Santa had to call on his Christmas Elves to pull off this Christmas miracle build. So I phone the homies @[Ryan Furrer](@ryandotfurrer) and @[Chris Nowicki](@chrisnowicki).

## Key Features

1. **Search Functionality**: Users can search for recipes by entering keywords in the searchbar. This feature is crucial for enhancing user experience, as it allows users to quickly find the recipes they are interested in. The search functionality is implemented using a simple form that captures user input and triggers a search query against the database.

2. **Displaying Results**: The application searches for any recipe titles and descriptions containing the user‚Äôs keyword and then displays any matching recipes. This is achieved by leveraging the power of React's state management and the efficient querying capabilities of DataStax‚Äôs Astra DB. All users have to do is enter the keyword they‚Äôd like to search and submit it; they should near instantly be returned a list of recipes where the keyword is in either the recipe‚Äôs title or description.

3. **DataStax Astra DB Integration**: Utilizes the DataStax Astra DB database to store and query recipe data. The integration with Astra DB was PRETTY seamless, thanks to its comprehensive API and support for various programming languages including TypeScript which we used in this project. This allows the application to efficiently store and retrieve large volumes of recipe data, ensuring a smooth user experience.


